WEBVTT

00:06.000 --> 00:12.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:35.202 --> 02:37.202
-Amy, what's wrong?
- I need your help!

02:37.842 --> 02:40.083
It's Connie,
she's run away again!

02:43.803 --> 02:45.003
She's only 15.

02:47.444 --> 02:50.644
How does my daughter fall
for this slime ball?

02:51.164 --> 02:52.004
Do you know him?

02:52.244 --> 02:54.645
Yeah, I met him once.
His name is Zip.

02:55.565 --> 02:56.845
That's a great name, huh?

02:57.885 --> 02:59.045
Jack, you're a cop.

02:59.285 --> 03:01.846
Grand theft auto.
You want missing persons.

03:02.806 --> 03:04.366
You know where he lives?

03:05.246 --> 03:09.767
Something like Trump Street,
or Trout Street or....

03:10.047 --> 03:12.767
- Turk? Turk Street?
- Yes, Turk Street. Turk Street.

03:12.887 --> 03:13.968
So tell missing persons.

03:14.088 --> 03:15.448
They've got a list a mile long.

03:15.568 --> 03:18.768
By the time they get to her, she'll
be the age I wanted her to leave.

03:18.888 --> 03:19.328
She'll be back.

03:19.608 --> 03:23.169
Three days, Jack.
I'm really scared.

03:23.689 --> 03:25.129
- Amy, I'm....
- I know.

03:25.849 --> 03:28.330
You're going on vacation,
some music festival.

03:29.450 --> 03:31.210
A week with you and your cello.

03:33.170 --> 03:35.371
That'll be so different for you.

03:43.012 --> 03:46.252
I know I'm just your neighbor.
I had no business asking.

03:47.532 --> 03:49.173
You have a great time, okay?

04:05.855 --> 04:09.175
I was planning on blacking him out.
I'm glad I didn't.

04:11.776 --> 04:14.696
It can't be that different
from looking for a car, right?

04:19.177 --> 04:19.976
Turk Street.

05:31.027 --> 05:32.747
I'm sorry.
I'm sorry, you okay?

05:33.547 --> 05:34.708
Oh! You mustn't bother.

05:34.828 --> 05:37.428
It's no bother.
Just get out of the rain. Come on.

05:45.669 --> 05:47.749
So you don't live
in the neighborhood.

05:47.909 --> 05:49.550
No, I'm looking for someone.

05:49.750 --> 05:51.470
You can just
set them down there.

05:51.670 --> 05:53.430
No, no.
I'll take them in the kitchen.

05:54.750 --> 05:56.271
Well, this way.

05:58.191 --> 06:00.351
Thomas, we have a visitor!

06:02.912 --> 06:06.032
Don't be alarmed,
we have a stranger in the house.

06:06.832 --> 06:12.273
- Thomas, dear. This is....
- Jack. Jack Friar.

06:13.833 --> 06:16.593
This is Mr. Quarre,
I'm Mrs. Quarre.

06:17.554 --> 06:21.034
Who is it you're looking for,
Jack, a friend?

06:21.314 --> 06:23.754
No, a suspect.
Well, not a suspect really.

06:24.555 --> 06:25.355
A young man.

06:26.875 --> 06:28.155
You're a policeman.

06:29.875 --> 06:32.316
- I really should be going.
- Oh, dear, don't go.

06:32.556 --> 06:34.436
I'll put on some water for tea.

06:34.796 --> 06:38.237
- Thanks but I have to....
- We won't hear of you leaving.

06:38.517 --> 06:42.517
I must thank you for your kindness.
Now, it's Indian tea.

06:43.357 --> 06:47.078
India Indians. Not the ones
we beat the crap out of.

06:50.038 --> 06:51.358
No, I really must go.

06:52.919 --> 06:57.439
This one's made
from hard wood... Oak, mahogany.

06:59.039 --> 07:01.320
I've got one made in Africa
from ivory.

07:02.960 --> 07:05.200
Maybe one of your cousins
carved it, huh?

07:06.761 --> 07:07.401
Jack!

07:14.522 --> 07:16.042
Tell us about the suspect.

07:16.762 --> 07:20.803
Is he a lone operator
or a member of some vicious gang?

07:22.843 --> 07:24.963
He seems to be an operator.
Yeah.

07:25.283 --> 07:26.683
What does he look like?

07:27.364 --> 07:28.204
I'll show you.

07:38.125 --> 07:41.165
He had blond hair, blue eyes.

07:42.406 --> 07:43.246
Stand up.

07:45.006 --> 07:45.846
Stand up.

07:48.727 --> 07:50.607
- How'd you find me?
- What?

07:55.327 --> 07:56.928
I said, how did you find me?

07:57.288 --> 07:59.288
Find you? Who are you?

08:02.168 --> 08:02.849
Smart ass!

08:28.972 --> 08:30.252
You like baseball?

08:30.492 --> 08:34.212
It's just a tiny little bump,
officer. I checked it out.

08:35.133 --> 08:36.293
Ready for your tea?

08:36.573 --> 08:38.534
- I don't like tea.
- Well who does?

08:39.054 --> 08:41.014
Tea is for Chinks,
give him a real drink.

08:41.134 --> 08:42.174
Would you like a shot?

08:42.294 --> 08:45.295
Make it a Mai Tai.
That's what we drank in Korea.

08:45.655 --> 08:48.335
- Who are you people?
- What happened here?

08:49.895 --> 08:52.336
This cop showed up,
looking for us.

08:52.856 --> 08:53.816
Me at least.

08:54.016 --> 08:57.096
That's why we kept him here, boss,
for you to decide.

09:00.297 --> 09:01.657
What did you hit him with?

09:05.457 --> 09:07.058
- No guns.
- No guns.

09:11.578 --> 09:14.579
Do I have to post
a list of rules at the front door?

09:14.899 --> 09:17.059
It might... help.

09:17.899 --> 09:19.339
Has anyone else a gun?

09:20.100 --> 09:20.740
Sure.

09:22.540 --> 09:24.260
Finally got a hit, shit head.

09:25.060 --> 09:26.780
Come on, Miller, knock him in!

09:27.061 --> 09:27.861
Listen, mister....

09:28.101 --> 09:30.141
-....Quarre. - Quarre.
- It's an alias.

09:30.301 --> 09:33.021
I really had a photograph,
not of that psychopath. But....

09:33.141 --> 09:34.422
Shh, there's a game on.

09:44.063 --> 09:44.943
Thank you, dear.

09:46.623 --> 09:47.343
Don't gloat.

09:47.663 --> 09:50.864
I'm not gloating,
don't be a sore loser.

09:55.505 --> 09:57.345
Maybe he's onto us for Seattle.

09:57.545 --> 09:59.305
You shouldn't have
let him see you.

09:59.425 --> 10:01.825
I wasn't just going
to let him walk out of here.

10:02.226 --> 10:05.506
The questions are:
what are we going to do with him?

10:05.826 --> 10:07.506
What if there are more of him?

10:10.387 --> 10:11.067
Kill him.

10:12.947 --> 10:13.987
We do not kill him.

10:15.027 --> 10:17.748
Because the penalties
for killing are so distasteful.

10:17.948 --> 10:21.028
Yeah, that's easy for you to say.
He didn't have your picture.

10:21.188 --> 10:22.548
He has no picture, Hoop.

10:23.389 --> 10:26.789
Perhaps we should outfit you
with a wooden club and a loincloth.

10:28.069 --> 10:28.749
Are you....

10:33.030 --> 10:34.870
Are you calling me backward?

10:44.392 --> 10:48.392
The best way to chase something,
Hoop, is to let it chase you.

10:50.072 --> 10:51.112
Greetings, Erin.

10:51.353 --> 10:54.273
Business. That's what you always say.
This is a business.

10:54.393 --> 10:57.073
Tell the old people
the schedule's been moved up a day.

10:57.193 --> 10:57.793
A day?

10:59.834 --> 11:02.274
- That's today.
- That's why you'll want to hurry.

11:04.434 --> 11:05.034
Sorry.

11:13.756 --> 11:16.756
You should try to have
a calming influence on Hoop..

11:17.916 --> 11:19.837
..rather than a inflammatory one.

11:21.877 --> 11:24.357
Is it your place to tell me
who not to inflame?

11:26.317 --> 11:28.518
As a matter of fact it is.

11:30.558 --> 11:32.118
With this rose, I thee wed.

11:33.038 --> 11:35.359
All things in good time.
Until then,..

11:36.759 --> 11:37.999
..Lover and loved.

11:38.599 --> 11:40.239
Pimp and whore.

11:53.001 --> 11:54.802
Coarseness does not become you.

12:34.527 --> 12:35.927
That sick fuck.

12:40.248 --> 12:41.888
It'll all be over soon.

12:42.088 --> 12:42.808
All of it?

12:43.248 --> 12:48.089
- This job, our last.
- You and him? That over?

12:48.769 --> 12:50.929
- What do you mean?
- You know what I mean.

12:51.130 --> 12:52.290
He hurts you.

12:53.290 --> 12:54.530
Keeps us down.

13:03.811 --> 13:04.851
I got to pack.

13:07.212 --> 13:08.052
I'll help.

13:12.012 --> 13:13.533
If Tyrone sees you
in my bedroom....

13:13.653 --> 13:16.093
We're just talking,
for Christ's sake.

13:19.334 --> 13:21.734
Okay. Later then.

13:28.415 --> 13:28.935
Hoop.

13:33.536 --> 13:35.016
I never chose Tyrone.

13:35.256 --> 13:38.296
Yeah, but sometimes
you laugh at me with him.

13:38.656 --> 13:41.737
He expects it of me.
Don't you understand that?

13:41.937 --> 13:43.297
Fucking cop's listening.

13:44.617 --> 13:45.217
Hoop.

13:48.538 --> 13:50.098
The cop's not our problem.

13:52.578 --> 13:53.218
Tyrone.

14:12.981 --> 14:15.582
So we leave the airstrip
no later than 8 pm.

14:19.102 --> 14:20.382
Don't smoke that in here.

14:20.942 --> 14:23.423
I sure as hell won't miss you
telling me what to do.

14:25.303 --> 14:27.983
- Control freak.
- Control is a good thing, Thomas.

14:28.383 --> 14:29.864
You could do with more of it.

14:31.224 --> 14:32.224
Control that.

14:37.185 --> 14:40.545
Then we land in Bermuda
no later than 2 am. Correct?

14:40.745 --> 14:41.665
Aye aye, sir.

14:41.945 --> 14:42.385
We refuel..

14:42.505 --> 14:45.466
..and Hoop's piloting the balance
of the journey to the Caymans.

14:45.586 --> 14:48.026
- Is he taking his meds?
- Yes, I assume so, why?

14:48.146 --> 14:49.466
He asked me
to teach him to fly,..

14:49.586 --> 14:52.147
..but I'm not responsible
if he flies off the handle.

14:52.667 --> 14:53.867
I will control Hoop.

15:14.510 --> 15:16.190
How'd you know where to find us?

15:16.710 --> 15:17.510
I didn't.

15:18.751 --> 15:20.431
You're not who I'm looking for.

15:21.671 --> 15:22.431
I have a pict --

15:23.911 --> 15:27.312
Yeah, right. A picture with a guy
with blond hair, blue eyes.

15:27.552 --> 15:29.672
I'm looking for a girl.

15:29.952 --> 15:31.632
Oh, now it's a girl.

15:31.752 --> 15:34.353
Gee, you know I just can't keep
your stories straight.

15:34.793 --> 15:35.273
Hoop!

15:36.113 --> 15:39.713
- Stop it!
- Alright. Settle down.

15:43.994 --> 15:45.114
These are too tight.

15:48.395 --> 15:51.595
Eventually I'm going to be
alone with you, cop.

15:51.875 --> 15:53.115
Get away from him.

15:56.076 --> 15:57.076
Is that better?

15:58.156 --> 15:58.796
Thanks.

16:13.678 --> 16:14.758
There is a picture.

16:16.919 --> 16:18.159
And there is a girl.

16:28.080 --> 16:31.521
Was it out of willfulness or out
of stupidity you let him see you?

16:32.721 --> 16:33.801
I'm sorry, Tyrone.

16:35.241 --> 16:37.642
But I think he seems
to have seen you too.

16:42.442 --> 16:43.403
No he hasn't.

16:44.523 --> 16:46.283
It seems he's smarter than you.

16:48.563 --> 16:50.964
She's like a spoiled child.

16:51.524 --> 16:53.844
Hateful towards those
who take care of her..

16:54.044 --> 16:56.844
..and yet totally dependent.
- Leave her alone.

16:57.725 --> 17:00.765
And Hoop is the spoiled boy.

17:01.485 --> 17:02.605
The spoiled boy,..

17:03.165 --> 17:06.406
..to whom I gave a future despite
the metal plate in his head..

17:06.646 --> 17:08.246
..and the diagnosed psychosis.

17:08.445 --> 17:09.205
Now, Hoop,..

17:09.486 --> 17:12.406
..was it the Belle of Tacos
or the King of Burgers..

17:12.686 --> 17:15.166
..which had most recently
rejected your services?

17:15.367 --> 17:17.087
What are you laughing at, cop?!

17:20.328 --> 17:23.647
Maybe it's good that our stay
in these close quarters nears its end.

17:23.768 --> 17:24.688
Brunch is ready.

17:25.048 --> 17:26.289
No, brunch is canceled.

17:26.409 --> 17:29.449
The unexpected appearance
by the officer has altered our plans.

17:29.569 --> 17:30.289
Excuse me.

17:30.729 --> 17:34.650
I have been cooking
since his God damned appearance.

17:35.090 --> 17:36.370
No one said anything.

17:42.051 --> 17:44.171
Well, perhaps brunch
is just what we need.

17:51.772 --> 17:53.733
Who would like to say
the blessing?

17:57.373 --> 17:58.813
How about our guest?

17:59.373 --> 18:00.814
He should say a prayer.

18:01.094 --> 18:04.334
- Leave him alone.
- You have nothing to worry about.

18:04.574 --> 18:07.214
I'm sure everything
will go as planned.

18:07.615 --> 18:09.175
I'll say the blessing.

18:12.295 --> 18:14.856
Thank you, Lord, for that
which we are about to receive....

18:14.976 --> 18:16.776
Ten million dollars, Amen!

18:31.498 --> 18:33.458
You always forget the ketchup.

18:35.979 --> 18:36.899
Bring me a beer.

18:38.659 --> 18:40.059
Please.

18:44.620 --> 18:45.540
No, thank you.

18:46.660 --> 18:49.740
He's probably not used
to eating a proper breakfast.

18:49.981 --> 18:51.021
This is delicious.

18:52.941 --> 18:54.901
Remember you're flying, Thomas.

18:55.181 --> 18:57.062
I flew 57 missions in Korea..

18:57.182 --> 18:58.542
..and I was drunk
every damn time.

18:58.662 --> 19:00.302
- Don't you tel --
- Let him drink.

19:00.782 --> 19:02.022
I'll fly the damn plane.

19:02.142 --> 19:05.303
I'll let you co-pilot, shut the fuck
up while I'm telling my story.

19:05.423 --> 19:06.183
Excuse me, dear,..

19:06.343 --> 19:08.463
..but nobody gives a titty
about your story.

19:08.583 --> 19:10.303
I don't want
this punk interrupting me.

19:12.624 --> 19:15.384
Come on, old man! You want to fly?
I'll let you fly.

19:15.584 --> 19:17.624
Come on.
Come on. First one's free.

19:19.865 --> 19:21.065
Are you children?!

19:21.745 --> 19:23.505
Must I put you in separate rooms?

19:32.067 --> 19:33.587
Take him into the kitchen.

19:35.307 --> 19:36.627
You brought the cops.

19:37.147 --> 19:37.907
Shut up!

19:38.827 --> 19:40.428
You defective little prick.

19:46.028 --> 19:47.789
It's our banker friend.
Delay him.

19:48.989 --> 19:50.469
Keep him out of the house.

19:51.669 --> 19:53.790
Your clothing is inappropriate.
Go change it.

19:56.150 --> 19:58.230
David.
What are you doing here?

19:58.350 --> 20:01.311
I needed to see Erin.
She left me a message, it's important.

20:01.431 --> 20:03.391
She's not available just now.

20:03.911 --> 20:04.751
Where is she?

20:05.431 --> 20:08.792
Frankly I don't know.
I just came in from shopping.

20:09.752 --> 20:12.072
I'm sure she'll get
in touch with you later.

20:12.312 --> 20:14.273
Why don't you
go back to your office?

20:14.473 --> 20:16.553
If Mr. Quarre knew
you were playing hooky..

20:16.673 --> 20:19.593
..he might not look so kindly
on you dating his granddaughter.

20:34.915 --> 20:35.796
David!

20:37.676 --> 20:39.756
Erin! Hey!

20:45.237 --> 20:46.397
It's happening today.

20:47.157 --> 20:48.757
- What?
- Yeah, now.

20:49.117 --> 20:49.798
Why?

20:50.198 --> 20:52.998
Well, I don't know why.
But Tyrone says it has to be.

20:54.518 --> 20:55.638
Look, I can't.

20:56.038 --> 20:58.159
If you want us to be together,
you have to.

21:01.079 --> 21:03.800
Go back to the bank
and we'll see you soon, okay?

21:10.240 --> 21:12.681
David,
I'm in the street in my robe.

21:13.641 --> 21:14.761
Look, I adore you.

21:29.723 --> 21:30.803
Thomas! Isabelle!

21:31.283 --> 21:33.844
If we're delayed,
simply wait at the landing field.

21:35.044 --> 21:37.644
Keep your cell phone on
in case of a problem. Erin!

21:38.965 --> 21:41.085
You will stay
and entertain our guest.

21:41.405 --> 21:43.885
Whoa, whoa, what about David?
He expects me.

21:44.805 --> 21:46.406
I will deal with David.

21:47.006 --> 21:48.006
- Hoop!
- Yeah.

21:50.486 --> 21:51.206
Good.

21:52.406 --> 21:53.807
So, shall we?

21:57.287 --> 21:58.327
Take my bags, Hoop.

22:00.728 --> 22:01.808
Both of them.

22:07.849 --> 22:09.369
Be available to take calls.

22:10.529 --> 22:13.649
David may need to hear
your devoted voice for reassurance.

22:27.651 --> 22:28.612
You are art.

22:35.493 --> 22:36.573
Do not fade.

23:29.900 --> 23:32.461
- Are you comfortable?
- Been better.

23:45.743 --> 23:47.143
Hey, you okay?

23:50.303 --> 23:51.783
May I have some water?

23:52.544 --> 23:55.424
Water?
You look a little stressed.

23:59.344 --> 24:03.185
- Look, miss....
- Erin, please. - Erin.

24:03.865 --> 24:07.986
You need to let me go before that
head case Hoop comes back to kill me.

24:08.306 --> 24:10.066
Tyrone won't let Hoop kill you.

24:11.586 --> 24:14.227
Tyrone is against killing.

24:31.989 --> 24:32.469
So...

24:36.110 --> 24:39.150
Do you want any kind of music?
You like some music?

24:41.550 --> 24:44.751
- Look, miss, please....
- I can't let you escape,..

24:45.151 --> 24:48.351
..because then I would have
to escape and no one escapes Tyrone.

24:48.591 --> 24:49.712
That's ridiculous.

24:50.792 --> 24:51.592
Is it?

24:58.273 --> 25:00.953
This is how Tyrone says
you shouldn't have left.

25:11.555 --> 25:14.555
It's alright, I get ten percent
off my pedicures now.

25:28.997 --> 25:31.238
- Are you taking your medication?
- Why?

25:31.718 --> 25:33.078
You appear agitated.

25:33.678 --> 25:35.358
Yeah, well you piss me off.

25:36.158 --> 25:38.719
They got a medication
to make you stop doing that?

25:40.799 --> 25:43.639
What do you plan on doing
with your share of the money?

25:48.280 --> 25:50.480
I want... to breed dogs..

25:53.241 --> 25:54.201
..back in Utah.

25:56.001 --> 25:56.841
Excellent!

26:00.922 --> 26:03.002
Is there a young lady
in the picture?

26:04.722 --> 26:06.603
Maybe there is,
maybe there isn't.

26:15.844 --> 26:16.284
D --

26:18.084 --> 26:18.924
David Brewster.

26:19.124 --> 26:20.685
We're here. Hoop is beginning.

26:20.845 --> 26:22.325
Why are we doing this today?

26:22.445 --> 26:23.045
What?

26:25.525 --> 26:26.765
What did you say?

26:27.085 --> 26:28.326
I need an explanation.

26:28.526 --> 26:31.246
Your explanation will be
your share of the money.

26:33.286 --> 26:35.087
- Is Erin there?
- No she's not.

26:35.207 --> 26:36.287
But I have complete faith..

26:36.407 --> 26:38.687
..you will be able
to swindle your bank without her.

26:38.807 --> 26:41.368
Just make sure you're available
for me when I enter.

27:01.250 --> 27:02.771
You don't look so good.

27:03.571 --> 27:05.851
That's because
you're used to looking at you.

27:10.732 --> 27:13.452
Maybe that drink
wasn't such a good idea.

27:13.852 --> 27:16.332
- What should I do?
- What should you do?

27:16.452 --> 27:19.293
Find that picture so you can see
I was telling the truth..

27:19.413 --> 27:21.053
..and you can tell your friends.

27:21.933 --> 27:25.334
I'll look a lot better when I'm not
waiting for someone to kill me.

27:33.975 --> 27:34.615
Alright.

28:03.579 --> 28:08.100
Listen, I couldn't find the picture.
Okay, I walked the whole block.

28:14.021 --> 28:14.741
Hey!

28:21.822 --> 28:22.342
Oh, God.

28:30.263 --> 28:33.703
Please, don't die.
Don't die, please.

28:35.624 --> 28:36.104
Shit!

28:49.946 --> 28:50.666
Shit!

29:58.075 --> 29:59.436
How you doing, leatherhead?

29:59.956 --> 30:03.716
I got the generator set up in case
this storm messes with the lights.

30:04.236 --> 30:05.236
How's it look?

30:05.877 --> 30:06.917
Oh, it looks great.

30:07.437 --> 30:09.597
I've been thinking
about some of those missions....

30:09.717 --> 30:11.237
- Has the plane been fueled?
- Yes.

30:11.357 --> 30:13.518
And I'll be here
just as long as you need me.

30:29.000 --> 30:30.040
Excuse me, sir.

30:45.482 --> 30:47.322
I put your kit in the fridge.

30:49.843 --> 30:51.403
You could have let me die.

30:53.203 --> 30:56.924
Cop dead from a diabetic coma.
It's perfect.

