01:06:08.224 --> 01:06:08.904
Tyrone.

01:06:11.984 --> 01:06:12.985
The cop had this.

01:06:14.625 --> 01:06:16.185
He wasn't looking for Hoop..

01:06:16.505 --> 01:06:19.585
..for beating up some clerk
in Seattle, he was looking for you.

01:06:31.307 --> 01:06:33.107
Maybe I shouldn't have told you.

01:06:43.349 --> 01:06:44.029
Tell him.

01:06:53.310 --> 01:06:56.951
I arranged for you to get the gun.
He wants you to kill the cop.

01:06:57.791 --> 01:06:58.391
Yeah.

01:07:01.471 --> 01:07:03.152
But it's not what we want.

01:07:05.272 --> 01:07:05.872
Yeah.

01:07:08.752 --> 01:07:09.353
Okay.

01:07:26.755 --> 01:07:27.275
What?

01:07:28.715 --> 01:07:29.475
Tire.

01:07:36.276 --> 01:07:37.797
....in the middle of nowhere.

01:07:38.917 --> 01:07:40.277
Why have you stopped here?

01:07:40.877 --> 01:07:42.877
I'm going to check
the spare in the trunk.

01:07:42.997 --> 01:07:44.478
What do you mean the spare?

01:07:46.158 --> 01:07:48.918
Didn't I tell you to check it
back at the gas station?

01:07:51.198 --> 01:07:53.279
Any last words, Brainiac?

01:07:54.399 --> 01:07:56.959
I'll spare you my wisdom,
you'll forsake it anyway.

01:07:57.119 --> 01:07:59.560
Oh no please,
I'm sure I'll miss it.

01:07:59.960 --> 01:08:02.200
I'll look at your life
as a novel,..

01:08:03.480 --> 01:08:05.160
..this being the tragic moment..

01:08:05.481 --> 01:08:06.961
..at which,
in the ultimate irony,..

01:08:07.081 --> 01:08:09.801
..our headstrong hero
shoots himself in the brain.

01:08:10.001 --> 01:08:12.922
So let me get this straight:
you're my brain?

01:08:13.962 --> 01:08:17.962
Not only that, I'm also
the restraint that you lack.

01:08:18.362 --> 01:08:19.082
Stand back.

01:08:27.084 --> 01:08:30.084
Without me,
you would be in prison or worse.

01:08:31.124 --> 01:08:33.805
You really think
you would thrive so without me?

01:08:34.444 --> 01:08:37.685
Witness tonight. Because
I wasn't standing right beside you..

01:08:38.444 --> 01:08:39.604
..you killed a man.

01:08:42.086 --> 01:08:45.566
And once you shoot me,
you'll have killed two men today.

01:08:46.966 --> 01:08:48.807
And the cop, three.

01:08:57.968 --> 01:09:03.169
Do you imagine that Erin
will ride into the sunset with you?

01:09:06.689 --> 01:09:08.089
Shut that music off!

01:09:10.450 --> 01:09:12.010
- Turn it down!
- Okay! Okay!

01:09:13.569 --> 01:09:15.850
Hoop! What are you doing?

01:09:17.011 --> 01:09:17.731
Nothing.

01:09:19.091 --> 01:09:21.571
Our friend
only got a little overexcited.

01:09:23.492 --> 01:09:25.372
It's better now, isn't it?

01:09:29.692 --> 01:09:30.212
Yeah.

01:09:32.533 --> 01:09:33.453
Get in the car.

01:09:35.533 --> 01:09:36.252
Not you.

01:09:41.493 --> 01:09:42.894
Were you behind this?

01:09:43.174 --> 01:09:45.055
You told me to give him the gun.

01:09:52.816 --> 01:09:54.896
So the policeman really is after me?

01:09:55.256 --> 01:09:55.776
Yes.

01:10:02.497 --> 01:10:03.377
We'll see.

01:10:05.578 --> 01:10:07.778
An unfortunate detour,
I'm afraid.

01:10:32.421 --> 01:10:33.342
I need the gun.

01:10:33.902 --> 01:10:35.742
No. Use another method.

01:10:37.022 --> 01:10:38.142
I've seen that you can.

01:10:39.182 --> 01:10:39.662
Go.

01:10:43.583 --> 01:10:45.583
Hoop, wait!

01:10:50.984 --> 01:10:52.184
Well, now my dear,..

01:10:52.984 --> 01:10:56.945
..witnessing an execution you caused
is only going to be awkward.

01:10:57.785 --> 01:10:59.665
What could you possibly say
to the man?

01:11:03.146 --> 01:11:03.706
Cop!

01:11:05.786 --> 01:11:07.106
I told you I'd be back.

01:11:07.466 --> 01:11:09.347
I hope you know how to die fast..

01:11:09.587 --> 01:11:11.707
..because we need
to be in Albany by eight.

01:11:13.187 --> 01:11:14.667
You know how to die fast?

01:11:15.227 --> 01:11:17.148
Die fast, cop. Fast.

01:11:17.428 --> 01:11:22.228
Faster! Faster! Faster!
Faster! Faster! Faster!

01:11:22.509 --> 01:11:23.269
Faster, cop!

01:11:48.272 --> 01:11:49.672
Spare yourself the effort.

01:11:57.393 --> 01:11:59.314
We lack time,
so forgive my brevity.

01:11:59.914 --> 01:12:03.354
Were you carrying a photograph
when you stumbled upon our house?

01:12:04.194 --> 01:12:04.755
Yeah.

01:12:05.355 --> 01:12:06.595
Now look at me.

01:12:10.515 --> 01:12:11.676
Was the picture of me?

01:12:22.157 --> 01:12:23.357
Was this the picture?

01:12:23.597 --> 01:12:26.638
That wasn't the picture,
that wasn't the fucking picture!

01:12:26.918 --> 01:12:28.038
Leave him alone!

01:12:32.919 --> 01:12:34.519
The truth is it hardly matters.

01:12:34.919 --> 01:12:38.679
A killing has already occurred. Not
just this one but another man as well.

01:12:38.799 --> 01:12:40.320
So the stakes have been raised.

01:12:40.560 --> 01:12:42.640
It does make sense
to clean up loose ends.

01:12:42.760 --> 01:12:44.000
And I'm a loose end.

01:12:44.600 --> 01:12:45.520
The loosest.

01:12:47.721 --> 01:12:48.321
Erin...

01:12:50.361 --> 01:12:51.081
Come here.

01:13:01.483 --> 01:13:04.403
Now, just put your finger there.

01:13:06.283 --> 01:13:08.084
Easy, this is your baptism.

01:13:08.804 --> 01:13:12.404
You think 'cause you've already killed
somebody, killing me is no big deal?

01:13:12.524 --> 01:13:15.925
You kill me and every cop
on the planet takes a sudden vacation.

01:13:16.045 --> 01:13:19.405
You become the case that never closes,
the guy they never stop huntin'.

01:13:19.525 --> 01:13:20.725
You be job one.

01:13:21.485 --> 01:13:24.406
Pay attention, Erin,
'cause this applies to you, too.

01:13:24.726 --> 01:13:27.126
When they catch you,
wherever they catch you..

01:13:27.326 --> 01:13:28.726
..they're going to subdue you.

01:13:28.846 --> 01:13:31.407
And they're going
to subdue you substantially.

01:13:32.087 --> 01:13:33.607
Then they're going
to tell you to run..

01:13:33.727 --> 01:13:36.648
..and that's going to confuse you,
'cause you never heard that before.

01:13:36.768 --> 01:13:39.728
Then your animal brain's going
to kick in with the survival mode.

01:13:39.848 --> 01:13:42.688
Telling you stupid shit like:
"Hey, they're letting me go".

01:13:42.808 --> 01:13:45.289
- So you'll run.
- And then what?

01:13:46.569 --> 01:13:48.209
Then they shoot you, dumb ass.

01:13:48.729 --> 01:13:52.690
Well, don't you think
they have to catch me first?

01:13:53.090 --> 01:13:56.170
Oh, you're thinking all that money
is going to help you hide?

01:13:56.370 --> 01:13:59.931
That's funny, 'cause those shit for
brains over there told me about your..

01:14:00.171 --> 01:14:00.811
..time frame.

01:14:01.531 --> 01:14:04.452
Now, if you planned on driving
to Albany in six hours,..

01:14:04.572 --> 01:14:07.212
..that means you're going
to use the New Jersey Turnpike.

01:14:07.332 --> 01:14:09.372
And you're probably
going to drive at night.

01:14:09.492 --> 01:14:10.812
But now you're late..

01:14:11.293 --> 01:14:13.173
..and you hadn't counted
on rush hour.

01:14:13.573 --> 01:14:16.773
So if you think you're still going
to make that drive in six hours..

01:14:16.893 --> 01:14:18.374
..you got another thing coming.

01:14:19.214 --> 01:14:22.734
Dearest, I don't remember
hearing anything about Albany.

01:14:23.094 --> 01:14:23.814
I knew it!

01:14:24.214 --> 01:14:26.255
You dirty double-crossing bastard!

01:14:26.455 --> 01:14:27.255
Put it down.

01:14:27.455 --> 01:14:29.455
Nobody's trying
to cross you, Thomas.

01:14:29.695 --> 01:14:31.775
Give him the disk. Now.

01:14:46.017 --> 01:14:48.378
Oh, God!
What have I done?

01:14:53.458 --> 01:14:54.219
Oh, God!

01:15:22.263 --> 01:15:25.103
This is a well-oiled machine!

01:15:27.823 --> 01:15:29.944
Look, why don't you
take me with you?

01:15:30.424 --> 01:15:30.864
What?

01:15:31.344 --> 01:15:34.464
You can't get the money on your own,
but you can with my help.

01:15:34.664 --> 01:15:37.105
My car's got flashing lights
and a siren,..

01:15:37.345 --> 01:15:39.505
..I can still get you
to Albany in time.

01:15:39.625 --> 01:15:41.345
You get as much of the money
as you can,..

01:15:41.465 --> 01:15:43.546
..I drive you to the border,
you go across.

01:15:44.386 --> 01:15:47.226
Hey, you promise me a share,
maybe I'll cross with you.

01:15:48.866 --> 01:15:49.867
And then what?

01:15:50.107 --> 01:15:52.427
First of all:
I need some more insulin.

01:15:52.787 --> 01:15:53.507
Secondly:

01:15:55.267 --> 01:15:58.748
..when we get across we let the girl
decide who she wants to go with.

01:16:08.029 --> 01:16:11.590
You propose driving through
a busy city with a captive policeman.

01:16:12.870 --> 01:16:14.830
You must think me a foolhardy man.

01:16:33.673 --> 01:16:36.273
Take a turn
at the next corner. Left.

01:16:48.435 --> 01:16:49.635
Now left again.

01:16:59.156 --> 01:17:00.957
I thought we were going
to the freeway.

01:17:03.877 --> 01:17:05.957
Turn again. Left.

01:17:17.079 --> 01:17:17.719
Go there.

01:17:29.401 --> 01:17:31.201
Out of the car, both of you.

01:17:47.803 --> 01:17:48.603
Further.

01:18:20.808 --> 01:18:21.408
Here.

01:18:26.449 --> 01:18:28.409
So how do you move
ten million dollars?

01:18:29.929 --> 01:18:32.010
Send the money
to a number of banks.

01:18:32.450 --> 01:18:34.930
In amounts small enough
not to draw attention.

01:18:36.890 --> 01:18:37.370
Hey.

01:18:38.811 --> 01:18:40.651
Why don't you try
and get some sleep.

01:18:50.212 --> 01:18:52.172
Oh, man!
It's worse than I thought.

01:18:57.013 --> 01:18:59.373
Hey, hang on,
it's going to be bumpy.

01:19:15.176 --> 01:19:16.136
Nicely done!

01:19:18.336 --> 01:19:19.136
Oh, man.

01:19:22.577 --> 01:19:25.617
Hey. Are you going to shoot me
in the back while I'm driving?

01:19:55.181 --> 01:19:56.342
Mr. Leeds, please.

01:19:56.542 --> 01:19:58.742
- Yes. Can you hold please?
- Yes, I'll hold.

01:19:58.862 --> 01:20:02.062
So Tyrone, who's going in
to grab the money. Me?

01:20:02.222 --> 01:20:05.503
Don't be absurd.
I trust you no more than I trust her.

01:20:05.743 --> 01:20:07.423
Yes, Mr. Clifford Leeds, please.

01:20:07.623 --> 01:20:10.584
This is Mr. Leeds.
Welcome back, Mr. Abernathy.

01:20:10.704 --> 01:20:12.504
It's been so long
since we've seen you.

01:20:14.184 --> 01:20:16.784
One more thing, I'm a bit ill.

01:20:16.944 --> 01:20:20.625
Would it be possible for me to pick
up the checks at the drive-through?

01:20:20.745 --> 01:20:22.625
- Sure, if that's a problem....
- Not at all.

01:20:22.745 --> 01:20:24.546
I'll alert the teller
to watch for you.

01:20:24.666 --> 01:20:28.226
She'll know me by my chauffeur,
a very earnest looking black man.

01:20:29.226 --> 01:20:30.986
Okay, thank you, Clifford.

01:20:35.707 --> 01:20:36.547
Good morning.

01:20:39.228 --> 01:20:42.388
Mr. Abernathy.
Mr. Leeds said to be expecting you.

01:20:42.668 --> 01:20:43.308
Excellent!

01:20:45.068 --> 01:20:46.629
- Have a good day.
- Thank you.

01:20:53.350 --> 01:20:54.510
May I see those?

01:20:59.431 --> 01:21:03.111
Jesus, I get ID'd
trying to deposit a check.

01:21:04.751 --> 01:21:05.951
At my own bank!

01:21:11.712 --> 01:21:12.912
Where to next, Tyrone?

01:21:13.032 --> 01:21:15.193
Continue straight,
I'll tell you when to turn.

01:21:19.873 --> 01:21:21.354
Red light!
Red light!

01:21:21.994 --> 01:21:22.274
Damn.

01:21:22.394 --> 01:21:24.394
- We had the right of way!
- You asshole!

01:21:24.514 --> 01:21:26.834
I'm actually beginning
to trust you, officer.

01:21:26.954 --> 01:21:28.875
Enough to take
that gun out of my back?

01:21:29.675 --> 01:21:30.395
No,..

01:21:31.795 --> 01:21:32.795
..but this much.

01:21:38.636 --> 01:21:41.877
- Hey, how are you holding up?
- Fine.

01:21:56.199 --> 01:21:59.799
You are going to give her her share
before we cross the border, right?

01:22:03.960 --> 01:22:05.080
Once we cross,..

01:22:05.600 --> 01:22:07.760
..you can either go with me,
go with him..

01:22:08.360 --> 01:22:09.881
..or go your own way.

01:22:30.283 --> 01:22:31.964
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

01:22:32.124 --> 01:22:34.804
I believe you have
some checks for me. Mr. Abernathy.

01:22:35.004 --> 01:22:36.244
- Abernathy?
- Yes.

01:22:38.125 --> 01:22:39.005
Watch your hand.

01:22:39.125 --> 01:22:40.485
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

01:22:42.325 --> 01:22:42.965
Move it.

01:22:46.086 --> 01:22:47.606
- Oh damn.
- What?

01:22:47.926 --> 01:22:49.006
Don't look.
Don't look.

01:22:49.646 --> 01:22:50.526
That teller.

01:22:50.886 --> 01:22:53.887
She's making the security guard
write down our license number.

01:23:14.050 --> 01:23:15.530
Can we do this quickly?

01:23:31.012 --> 01:23:33.012
We have time
to make it to another bank.

01:23:35.333 --> 01:23:36.693
It's not worth the risk.

01:24:08.097 --> 01:24:10.218
Now, then,
let's go to the border.

01:25:01.025 --> 01:25:01.825
We cool?

01:25:05.425 --> 01:25:06.346
We're cool.

01:25:10.826 --> 01:25:12.586
You're going
to have to lose the shotgun.

01:25:12.706 --> 01:25:16.027
It's essential to our understanding.
I'll just cover it.

01:25:16.227 --> 01:25:17.787
Give me the map, Erin.

01:25:19.507 --> 01:25:21.748
You've done excellent work,
officer Friar.

01:25:21.948 --> 01:25:24.148
Perhaps you'd like
to stay in my employ...

01:25:26.268 --> 01:25:28.749
Jack! You don't have
to kill him, please!

01:25:33.709 --> 01:25:34.470
I'm okay!

01:25:34.590 --> 01:25:36.150
- Don't move, Jack!
- I'm alright.

01:25:37.150 --> 01:25:39.630
Tyrone! Give yourself up!

01:25:41.511 --> 01:25:43.151
Halt! Police!

01:25:43.391 --> 01:25:44.991
Jack, don't kill him!

01:25:45.231 --> 01:25:46.191
Tyrone!

01:25:46.791 --> 01:25:48.832
It's over,
there's no place to go!

01:25:52.152 --> 01:25:52.992
Freeze!

01:26:06.714 --> 01:26:08.674
- Let go of me!
- Put it down!

01:26:09.195 --> 01:26:10.675
Put it down now!

01:26:10.995 --> 01:26:14.395
Do it! Step away from the car,
both hands up!

01:26:14.915 --> 01:26:16.996
Please, remain in your car!

01:26:37.239 --> 01:26:39.919
You understand that
while under Canada's jurisdiction..

01:26:40.039 --> 01:26:42.119
..we respect your interest
in this situation.

01:26:42.239 --> 01:26:45.200
No warrants or reports
have been made as of yet.

01:26:47.120 --> 01:26:48.880
We'll wait
for your recommendation.

01:26:51.040 --> 01:26:53.601
Lucky thing having
those license plates behind you.

01:27:06.003 --> 01:27:07.763
Tell them I was a hostage.

01:27:08.643 --> 01:27:09.683
It's the truth.

01:27:11.043 --> 01:27:12.924
I tried to leave him, you know.

01:27:13.204 --> 01:27:15.164
I tried to leave him.
I couldn't.

01:27:17.684 --> 01:27:19.725
I've got a million dollars
right here.

01:27:20.165 --> 01:27:21.365
You've got yours.

01:27:21.605 --> 01:27:23.965
We could spend
our lives on vacation.

01:27:24.845 --> 01:27:26.125
The same vacation.

01:27:33.967 --> 01:27:37.607
You have a way
of making me feel really good..

01:27:40.648 --> 01:27:41.968
..when you want something.

01:27:43.368 --> 01:27:46.328
- It's not like that.
- Oh, but it is.

01:27:48.649 --> 01:27:50.169
Only you don't know it.

01:27:55.970 --> 01:27:57.610
When we danced the cello..

01:28:00.530 --> 01:28:01.971
..you could have killed me.

01:28:04.491 --> 01:28:07.451
Whatever you saw in me then,
see it now.

01:28:10.252 --> 01:28:11.492
Help me, Jack.

01:29:08.500 --> 01:29:09.460
Arrest her.

